nd a brief description for the policy rule type.","pos":[10609,10671]},{"content":"For example, for a second-shift differential, you might enter <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>2nd Shift<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> as the name and <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Second shift differential<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> as the description.","pos":[10672,10813],"source":" For example, for a second-shift differential, you might enter **2nd Shift** as the name and **Second shift differential** as the description."},{"content":"Query name","pos":[10818,10828]},{"content":"Select <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Premium earnings<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[10837,10865],"source":"Select **Premium earnings**."},{"content":"This query is the default Application Object Tree (AOT) query that should be used as the starting point to develop policy rules for this policy rule type.","pos":[10866,11020]},{"pos":[11049,11127],"content":"Setting up earning code groups to identify earnings that qualify for a premium","linkify":"Setting up earning code groups to identify earnings that qualify for a premium","nodes":[{"content":"Setting up earning code groups to identify earnings that qualify for a premium","pos":[0,78]}]},{"content":"Earning code groups are used to identify earnings that qualify for the premium.","pos":[11129,11208]},{"content":"You set up earning code groups on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Earning code groups<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page.","pos":[11209,11276],"source":" You set up earning code groups on the **Earning code groups** page."},{"content":"You must create additional earning code groups to correctly identify the earnings for all your premiums that are based on earnings.","pos":[11277,11408]},{"content":"An earning code group can be used by more than one premium.","pos":[11409,11468]},{"content":"For example, if you have different shift differentials for union workers and non-union workers, those premiums will probably use the same earning code group.","pos":[11469,11626]},{"content":"Earning codes 